European Coal Derivatives Gain 0.6% for Second Straight Advance

-- B y   A l i s t a i r   H o l l o w a y
-- 
2011-04-28T08:31:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-28/european-coal-derivatives-gain-0-6-for-second-straight-advance.html
Benchmark European coal derivatives
had a second consecutive gain.  Coal for delivery to Amsterdam, Rotterdam or Antwerp with
settlement next year rose 75 cents, or 0.6 percent, to $131.75 a
metric ton by 9:23 a.m. in  London .  The data are drawn from information supplied by ICAP Plc,
 GFI Group Inc. (GFIG) , Spectron Group Ltd., Credit Suisse Group AG, IHS
McCloskey, Bloomberg, Tradition Financial Services and Tullett
Prebon Plc.  To contact the reporter on this story:
